The defendant Dustin R. East was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dustin R. East is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

2:01 PM DA calls cases: 22CF16 and 22CF83 Defendant Dustin R. East in court.  Attorney Stephen Donald Willett in court for Dustin R. East.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. Court proceeds with 22CF16. DA Kelz calls witness: Robert Zoubek a Park Falls Officer. Direct questioning of the witness by DA Kelz. Witness identifies the defendant on record. Cross examination by Attorney Willett. Witness excused. Statement by DA Kelz. Statement by Attorney Willett. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed. Defense taken a moment to go over the copy of the information provided to them by the State. Information acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Proceed to arraignment. Court continues with case 22CF83. DA Kelz calls witness: Erik Drake a Price County Officer. Witness sworn. Direct questioning of the witness by DA Kelz. Witness identifies the defendant on record. Cross examination of the witness by Attorney Willett. Witness excused. Statement by DA Kelz. No statement by Attorney Willett. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Attorney Willett requests that arraignment be set for another date unless he is allowed to file a substitution of judge after arraignment. No objection by DA Kelz. Court orders Attorney Willett to have the appropriate paperwork filed by the close of business 08/26/2022. Proceed to arraignment.
Preliminary hearing on August 22, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
